abstract: OL Groupe, the parent company of French Ligue 1 team Olympique Lyonnais, has completed the takeover of National Women's Soccer League (NWSL) franchise Reign FC in a deal worth $3.51 million, OL Groupe and Reign said on Thursday.
snippet: OL Groupe, the parent company of French Ligue 1 team Olympique Lyonnais, has completed the takeover of National Women's Soccer League (NWSL) franchise Reign FC in a deal worth $3.51 million, OL Groupe and Reign said on Thursday.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - OL Groupe, the parent company of French Ligue 1 team Olympique Lyonnais, has completed the takeover of National Women's Soccer League (NWSL) franchise Reign FC in a deal worth $3.51 million, OL Groupe and Reign said on Thursday.
headline_main: Lyon Parent Company Acquires NWSL's Reign FC
headline_print_headline: Lyon Parent Company Acquires NWSL's Reign FC

abstract: The federal government is reporting a 2.7% increase in the nation’s homeless population driven by a spike in California, according to an annual count that took place in January 2019.
snippet: The federal government is reporting a 2.7% increase in the nation’s homeless population driven by a spike in California, according to an annual count that took place in January 2019.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The federal government is reporting a 2.7% increase in the nation’s homeless population driven by a spike in California, according to an annual count that took place in January 2019.
headline_main: HUD Reporting 2.7% Percent Uptick in Homeless Population
headline_print_headline: HUD Reporting 2.7% Percent Uptick in Homeless Population

abstract: A 26-year-old Connecticut man who allegedly pledged allegiance to the Islamic State group's leader has been charged with attempting to provide material support to the terrorist group in Syria, federal prosecutors announced Thursday.
snippet: A 26-year-old Connecticut man who allegedly pledged allegiance to the Islamic State group's leader has been charged with attempting to provide material support to the terrorist group in Syria, federal prosecutors announced Thursday.
lead_paragraph: HARTFORD, Conn. — A 26-year-old Connecticut man who allegedly pledged allegiance to the Islamic State group's leader has been charged with attempting to provide material support to the terrorist group in Syria, federal prosecutors announced Thursday.
headline_main: Connecticut Man Accused of Supporting Islamic State Group

abstract: Foxconn Technology Group, the world's largest electronics manufacturer, could still qualify for up to $3 billion in state tax credits in Wisconsin if it makes changes to its deal with the state to reflect current plans for a plant that's under construction, Gov. Tony Evers said Thursday.

abstract: Miner Centamin Plc should extend a deadline for Canada's Endeavour Mining Corp to make a firm takeover offer, a top shareholder with both companies said on Thursday, increasing pressure on the London-listed miner to engage in talks.
